'''.<ref>{{cite web|url =https://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/Competition.aspx?ID=1035&PID=-1 | title =Competition format | website =cev.eu | publisher =CEV | access-date = 15 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n* [[#CEV Cup|CEV Cup]] (1980\u201381 to 2006\u20132007)\n* [[#CEV Challenge Cup|CEV Challenge Cup]] (2007\u201308 to present)\n\n==Title holders==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n* 1980\u201381 {{flagicon|FRA}} [[AS Cannes Volley-Ball|AS Cannes]]\n* 1981\u201382 {{flagicon|NED}} [[VISADE Voorburg|Star Lift Voorburg]]\n* 1982\u201383 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Modena Volley|Panini Modena]]\n* 1983\u201384 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Modena Volley|Panini Modena]]\n* 1984\u201385 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Modena Volley|Panini Modena]]\n* 1985\u201386 {{flagicon|ITA}} Kutiba Falconara\n* 1986\u201387 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Volley Gonzaga Milano|Ener-Mix Milano]]\n* 1987\u201388 {{flagicon|URS}} [[VC Avtomobilist Saint Petersburg|Avtomobilist Leningrad]]\n* 1988\u201389 {{flagicon|URS}} [[VC Avtomobilist Saint Petersburg|Avtomobilist Leningrad]]\n* 1989\u201390 {{flagicon|FRG}} Moerser SC\n* 1990\u201391 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Volley Treviso|Sisley Treviso]]\n* 1991\u201392 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Pallavolo Parma|Maxicono Parma]]\n* 1992\u201393 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Volley Treviso|Sisley Treviso]]\n* 1993\u201394 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Pallavolo Padova|Ignis Padova]]\n{{col-break}}\n* 1994\u201395 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Pallavolo Parma]]\n* 1995\u201396 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Piemonte Volley|Alpitour Traco Cuneo]]\n* 1996\u201397 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Porto Ravenna Volley]]\n* 1997\u201398 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Volley Treviso|Sisley Treviso]]\n* 1998\u201399 {{flagicon|ITA}} Palermo Volley\n* 1999\u201300 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Roma Volley]]\n* 2000\u201301 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Volley Lube|Lube Banca Marche Macerata]]\n* 2001\u201302 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Piemonte Volley|Noicom Cuneo]]\n* 2002\u201303 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Volley Treviso|Sisley Treviso]]\n* 2003\u201304 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Modena Volley|Kerakoll Modena]]\n* 2004\u2